\begin_inset LatexCommand \label{sec:Conclusions}

\end_inset 

Conclusions
\layout Standard

We have sketched a promising new method for the detection of transient phaenomen
a, with a wide range of characteristic time-scale.
 The method is very simple to implement, because it requires a minimum of
 calibration, and a trivial uv-data subtraction operation.
 This is important, in view of the 'impossible' amount of calibration processing
 that is required for the more traditional transient detection techniques,
 especially for relatively short-term transients.
 In addition, the method is potentially more sensitive, and provides more
 'handles' to analyse the detailed time-profile of transient sources.
 
\layout Standard

Eearly results are encouraging.
 The follow-up effort should be directed at developing methods for the analysis
 of residual images.
\layout Standard

It is possible, even likely, that the proposed transient detection method
 is a member of an entire family of relatively cheap differential methods,
 which could be crucial in dealing with the vast data-volumes produced by
 LOFAR and SKA.
